itemDescription: Born: 19 July 1913 in Liverpool, England; Died: 18 April 2000 in Nottingham, England

wikipedia_page.main: Doris Mary Cannell (19 July 1913 – 18 April 2000) was an educator and historian of early 19th century mathematical physics, in particular of George Green.

response: His work and influence on 19th-century applied physics had been largely forgotten until the publication of his biography by Mary Cannell in 1993.
